		<h4><div>Cellist Asier Polo<br>&ldquo;had audience at first note&rdquo;</div></h4>
		<p>When Anne Manson first heard cellist Asier Polo performing in Galicia, Spain, making him part of an MCO season became a priority. The audience&rsquo;s response to our 2012 concert was over the top, and now popular demand brings him back!</p>
		<p>In her <i>Winnipeg Free Press</i> review of that first concert, Holly Harris wrote about his &ldquo;... fierce artistry and utter surrender to music-making.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>Get ready! The passion that made that concert so memorable will be in abundance as Polo will perform not one, but two wonderfully different cello concertos this time around!</p>
		<p><b>1689 Francesco Ruggieri cello</b></p>
		<p>Asier Polo will work his wonders on a cello just about as old as, or even older than, the music he will be playing! Some things certainly do seem to last ...</p>
		<p>Although Francesco Ruggieri made violins and violas, his importance stems from his development of a smaller version of the cello that is now the standard. All instruments created by Ruggieri are highly desirable owing to their superior construction and tone (Wikipedia).</p>

